    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-17T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-17T11:00:00-05:00" n="789"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d789">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.001C13/124: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Nuevo Laredo</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wormuth</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-17T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 17, 1932—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reference General <persName corresp="#p_CPE1">Calles</persName>’ approaching
                    visit to United States through port of Laredo and Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_CR1">Clark</persName>’s instructions to you.</p>
                <p>Please report immediately by telegraph whether in your opinion District Attorney
                        <persName corresp="#p_VJA1">Valls</persName> will endeavor to create trouble
                    or any kind of unpleasant situation.</p>
                <p>Please request American border officials to facilitate in every way possible the
                    crossing of the border by the entire <persName corresp="#p_CPE1"
                        >Calles</persName> party.</p>
                <p>Appropriate action is being taken by the Department directly with the Treasury
                    and Labor Departments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
